### Health Check - Verify backend is running
GET http://localhost:3001/ping

### Get All Todo Lists - Should return seeded data
GET http://localhost:3001/api/lists

### Get All Todo Lists with Accept Header
GET http://localhost:3001/api/lists
Accept: application/json

### Test 404 Route - Should return not found error
GET http://localhost:3001/api/nonexistent

### Health Check with verbose headers
GET http://localhost:3001/ping
User-Agent: VSCode REST Client
Accept: application/json

### Test CORS headers
GET http://localhost:3001/api/lists
Origin: http://localhost:3000

### Create a new todo list (default name "New List")
POST http://localhost:3001/api/lists
Content-Type: application/json

### Create another new todo list to test ordering
POST http://localhost:3001/api/lists
Content-Type: application/json

### Update a todo list name - REPLACE WITH ACTUAL LIST ID
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/lists/REPLACE_WITH_LIST_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Shopping List"
}

### Update list with validation error - empty name
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/lists/REPLACE_WITH_LIST_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": ""
}

### Update list with validation error - name too long
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/lists/REPLACE_WITH_LIST_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "This is a very long list name that exceeds the 100 character limit and should cause a validation error to be returned by the API endpoint"
}

### Update list with HTML sanitization test
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/lists/REPLACE_WITH_LIST_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "<script>alert('test')</script>Safe List Name"
}

### Update non-existent list (404 error)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/lists/non-existent-id
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "This should fail"
}

### Delete a todo list - REPLACE WITH ACTUAL LIST ID
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/lists/REPLACE_WITH_LIST_ID

### Delete non-existent list (404 error)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/lists/non-existent-id

### Delete with invalid ID format (400 error)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/lists/invalid-id-format

